<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Oenonidae" genus="Arabella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Arabella (Arabella) iricolor" order="Eunicida" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="iricolor" subGenus="Arabella">Arabella (Arabella) iricolor</taxonomicName>
was described to the south coast of Devonshire (UK) as 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Nereis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nereis iricolor" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="iricolor">Nereis iricolor</taxonomicName>
(Montagu, 1804). The description of specimens from the 
<pageBreakToken pageId="3" pageNumber="4" start="start">Caribbean</pageBreakToken>
Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Augener, H" journalOrPublisher="Bijdragen Tot De Kennis Der Fauna Van Curacao" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="39 - 82" title="Polychaeten von Curacao." volume="25" year="1927">Augener 1927</bibRefCitation>
) closely reSEMbles specimens in this study, which were identified as this species due to the characteristics: ventralmost chaeta tapering gradually to guards in median and posterior chaetigers, the absence of hooded acicular chaetae, maxilla MxI unidentate and posterior post-chaetal lobe shorter than chaetae. Body surface whitish was observed in small fixed individuals, probably juveniles (Fig. 2
<normalizedToken originalValue="A–C">A-C</normalizedToken>
). (
<bibRefCitation author="Montagu, G" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Linnean Society of London" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="61 - 85" title="Description of several marine animals found on the south coast of Devonshire." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1804.tb00282.x" volume="7" year="1804">Montagu 1804</bibRefCitation>
). The species was recorded in ecological studies of the continental shelf, intertidal zone, coral reefs, estuaries, and mangroves (
<bibRefCitation author="Paiva, PC" journalOrPublisher="Revista de Biologia Marina y Oceanografia" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" url="https://doi.org/10.1590/s0373-55241993000100006" year="1993">Paiva 1993</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Santa-Isabel, LM" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="645 - 653" title="Polychaetes from the Guarajuba coral reefs, Bahia, Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-94-017-1982-7_28" volume="67" year="2000">Santa-Isabel et al. 2000</bibRefCitation>
), but apparently, the material was not deposited in any collection and was not available for comparison. Previous record from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Maranhão">Maranhao</normalizedToken>
reports specimens found in mangroves (
<bibRefCitation author="Oliveira, VM" journalOrPublisher="Boletim do Laboratorio de Hidrobiologia" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="75 - 93" title="Macroendofauna bentica de substratos moveis de um manguezal sob impacto das atividades humanas no sudoeste as ilha de Sao Luis, Maranhao, Brasil." volume="12" year="1999">Oliveira and Mochel 1999</bibRefCitation>
). This species has been described with worldwide distribution and is probably a complex of species (
<bibRefCitation author="Colbath, GH" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="283 - 299" title="A revision of Arabellamutans (Chamberlin, 1919) and related species (Polychaeta: Arabellidae)." volume="102" year="1989">Colbath 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zanol, J" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="745 - 772" title="New and previously known species of Oenonidae (Polychaeta: Annelida) from Lizard Island, Great Barrier Reef, Australia." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4019.1.26" volume="4019" year="2015">Zanol and Ruta 2015</bibRefCitation>
). Studies on the variation of the symmetry in maxillae and modified ventral chaetae should be conducted to know the polymorphism in species of the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Oenonidae" genus="Arabella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Arabella" order="Eunicida" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Arabella</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Steiner, TM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="2537 - 2551" title="Arabellaaracaensis, a new species with growth rings on its mandibles, and some remarks on the endoparasitic Labrorostratusprolificus (Polychaeta: Oenonidae) from southeast Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222930903219988" volume="43" year="2009">Steiner and Amaral 2009</bibRefCitation>
). That would be a challenge to species identification and new descriptions, once 
<taxonomicName family="Oenonidae" lsidName="" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="family">Oenonidae</taxonomicName>
species are usually collected in low densities (
<bibRefCitation author="Zanol, J" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Morphology" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1023 - 1043" title="Homology of prostomial and pharyngeal structures in Eunicida (Annelida) based on innervation and morphological similarities." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/jmor.10843" volume="271" year="2010">Zanol 2010</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zanol, J" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="745 - 772" title="New and previously known species of Oenonidae (Polychaeta: Annelida) from Lizard Island, Great Barrier Reef, Australia." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4019.1.26" volume="4019" year="2015">Zanol and Ruta 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
